84.7	Bret_Easton_Ellis	Bret Easton Ellis	Bret Easton Ellis (born March 7, 1964 in Los Angeles, California) is an American novelist and short story writer. His works have been translated into 27 different languages. He was regarded as one of the so-called literary Brat Pack, which also included Tama Janowitz and Jay McInerney. He is a self-proclaimed satirist, whose trademark technique, as a writer, is the expression of extreme acts and opinions in an affectless style. Ellis employs a technique of linking novels with common, recurring characters.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cb/Ellis.jpg/220px-Ellis.jpg
